message.content:
Analysis of the Target Image:

• Block Count & Layers  
  – There are four total pieces: two orange cylinders forming the base “wheels,” one horizontal yellow rectangular block spanning those cylinders, and one blue cube perched on top at the right‐hand side.  
  – The structure has three main “layers”:  
    1) Bottom layer: the pair of orange cylinders side by side.  
    2) Middle layer: one yellow rectangular block bridging across those cylinders.  
    3) Top layer: a blue cube resting on the right end of the yellow block.  

• Spatial Relationships  
  – The two orange cylinders sit in parallel, aligned left‐to‐right.  
  – The yellow block lies flat on top of (and perpendicular to) the cylinder axes, connecting both cylinders in one horizontal span.  
  – The blue cube sits squarely atop the right side of the yellow block (aligned so that its edges line up with the block’s edges).  

Selection of Required Blocks:

From the dictionary images, the pieces that match both shape and orientation (without further rotation) are:  
• Blue cube → Index 1  
• Horizontal yellow rectangular block → Index 6  
• Left orange cylinder (horizontal orientation) → Index 13  
• Right orange cylinder (horizontal orientation) → Index 14  

Assembly Order:

{  
  Step1: Move block with index 13,  
  Step2: Move block with index 14,  
  Step3: Move block with index 6,  
  Step4: Move block with index 1  
}
